==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disinfect
<hw>Dis`in*fect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Disinfected</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Disinfecting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To free from infectious or
contagious matter; to destroy putrefaction; to purify; to make
innocuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the infectious matter and the infectious matter and the
odoriferous matter are one . . . then to deodorize is to
<qex>disinfect</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ure.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>disinfectant</ent>⟦br⟧
